org.activebpel.rt.bpel.def.io.readers.def
Class AeReaderVisitor

java.lang.Object
  org.activebpel.rt.bpel.def.io.readers.def.AeReaderVisitor
All Implemented Interfaces:
IAeBPELConstants, IAeConstants, IAeDefVisitor, IAeErrorReportingDefVisitor, IAeReaderDefVisitor
Direct Known Subclasses:
AeBPWSReaderVisitor, AeWSBPELReaderVisitor
public abstract class AeReaderVisitor
extends java.lang.Object
implements IAeReaderDefVisitor, IAeBPELConstants

Responsible for setting all of the properties on the newly created AeDef objects from the current xml element and adding then def to their parent def.

Method Detail

hasErrors

public boolean hasErrors()
Description copied from interface: IAeErrorReportingDefVisitor
Returns true if there are errors encountered during the parse. These errors are significant enough to not add definition object to the process def. One example of an error like this would be encountering multiple child activities when only one is allowed.

cloneElement

protected org.w3c.dom.Element cloneElement(org.w3c.dom.Element aElem)
Clones the element passed in. We don't want to use the standard clone() method since the resulting document literal element would have the bpel namespace. As such, this method needs to make an exact copy of the element but using the null namespace. In order to do this, we'll make a custom "deep" clone of the element by walking all of its children and recreating them in a new Document.

Parameters:
aElem -
